Kabul   – Twenty-four civilians were killed and 68 others wounded in a suicide bomb explosion at a funeral in Afghanistan’s eastern province of Nangarhar on Tuesday, the country’s Interior Ministry said. “Terrorists conducted an attack against the funeral of Commander Shaikh Akram in surrounding areas of Kuz Kunar district, Nangarhar province, at around 11.00 a.m. on Tuesday. As a result, 24 civilians were killed and 68 others wounded,’’ the ministry said in a statement. Akram was an anti-militant figure in the region and was heading local pro-government militiamen, who have been fighting militants. He died on Monday night from a heart attack. The ministry strongly condemned the attack and described it as an inhuman act, according to the statement. No group has claimed responsibility for the attack so far. Militants of both the Taliban outfit and Islamic State (IS) group have presence in the mountainous province. (Xinhua/NAN) Jalalabad   -      Gunmen attacked an education department office in the eastern Afghan city of Jalalabad on Wednesday and were holding out against security forces who had surrounded the compound, officials said. Two explosions were heard near the scene and at least two people had been killed and five wounded, the… July 11, 2018 In "Foreign" ANKARA - Turkey has condemned a suicide bomb attack in eastern Afghan province of Nangarhar which killed three Turkish engineers and injured another one on Monday, according to Turkish Foreign Ministry. ``We strongly condemn this flagrant attack and expect Afghan officials to arrest the assailants immediately’’, the statement issued by… June 3, 2014 In "Foreign" Kabul -  At least 80 people were killed in a bombing in the Afghan capital during a demonstration, the Interior Ministry said on Saturday of the attack claimed by the Islamic State extremist group. An estimated 231 people were wounded after two suicide bombers targeted a peaceful demonstration in Kabul's… July 24, 2016 In "Foreign"